[23:55:48] [Render thread/INFO] (Minecraft) [System] [CHAT] Dialog elise_1: /{"title":"Elise","body":"Hey there, traveller. You've stumbled into our little base, the one we like to call Downstairs.\n\nWe're part of a bigger group called the Expedition Grand. We'd go down and explore various caves, structures, and ancient artifacts.\nThis is one of our hubs that we stay in, where we keep mission supplies and recruits.\nOr rather, that we used to stay in.\n\nYou see, back in 2001, we were a very popular group. We were getting lots of support and funding. Everyone loved us.\n\nThen it happened.\n\nYou see, when we would send out expeditioners, we would always give them these three things:\nAn air-filtering mask, an oxygen tank, and a headlamp.\nSometimes we would give them more, for different types of missions. But we always gave them these three things.\n\nBut something happened that day. July 23, 2001, near the Downstairs camp.\nA fatal incident occurred. One of our expeditioners, a friend of mine named Jonathan, suddenly pressed the panic button from inside his jacket.\nHe had stopped breathing.\nAnd we couldn't get to him in time.\nHe didn't make it.\n\nNo one knew what happened. He was 24 and perfectly healthy, as we assure all of our recruits are.\n\nThis didn't stop the press.\n\nWe lost everything. All our funding, most of our recruits, and all our community support.\nWe couldn't keep going; we had to stop.\n\nHowever, this didn't stop my mind.\nI was pacing for hours. How did this happen? What could've gone wrong?\nWhy did Jonathan have to die?\n\nI decided that I would conduct a full investigation.\n\nWhat I found was shocking. In the exact place that he pressed the panic button, there was a small hole in the stone wall behind him.\nAnd I found that this hole was leaking a weird type of gas; one that we had never seen before.\n\nThe particles were so small that they were able to go through the mask's filter.\nAnd the gas was so deadly that it was able to close a person's airway in seconds.\n\nI decided to go to our group's old scientist, named Fred. I told him that we knew why Jonathan died.\nFred decided to go down with us again.\n\nI told him everything; the hole, the masks, the gas; everything.\nHe didn't know what to think of it.\n\nHe collected some in a jar of his and took it home to testing.\nI asked Fred to give me any information he found out when he tested the myserious gas. He agreed.\n\nI decided to stay down here, trying to figure this out.\n\nI called Fred each day for 3 years, asking if he found out anything about the gas.\nOne day, he didn't pick up. This was... odd for him.\n\nI called the police to check in on him.\nThey knocked.\nNo answer.\nThey broke inside.\n\nFred was dead on his couch.\nHe had been reaching for his phone when he died.\n\nSomehow, the gas had broken out of the jar it was in, and made its way in the air.\nAll the way to Fred's face.\n\nThis broke me.\nI couldn't bear to go back up to the surface.\nNot after 2 people had lost their lives due to my mission.\n\nI vowed to never deal with the caves again.\n\nBut I live in them.\nThey are my home.\n\nAnd I won't leave.\nNot until I die.","actions":{}}
